title: Firefox Takes Long to Load a Specific Client Service Page After Recent Update
content:
Hi everyone,

After the most recent Firefox update, I started noticing that one specific service page from a client site loads unusually slow only in Firefox. Other pages on the same domain load fine, and the same page opens instantly in Chrome and Edge.

The slowdown happens on the Buffalo Airport Taxi & Limousine Service Buffalo Airport Taxi & Limousine Service page . The page does eventually load, but the initial connection hangs for a few seconds before anything appears. Once it’s cached, the speed improves, but the first load is consistently slow.

I’ve already tried: • Clearing the cache • Restarting the browser • Disabling all extensions • Testing in Private mode • Flushing DNS and changing DNS servers

The strange part is that everything on the server side looks normal, and network diagnostics show no issue. This seems to have started right after the Firefox update, so I’m wondering if there’s something related to SSL, connection negotiation, or new caching behaviour in this version.

Has anyone else seen Firefox slow down on specific pages after updating? Any settings or flags I should check?

Thanks in advance.
